name: ReportingCreativeSet
desc: The response to a request to fetch Creative Set-level reports.

items.name: adGroupCreativeSetId
items.desc: The unique identifier for the ad group Creative Set.

items.name: adGroupId
items.desc: The unique identifier for the ad group.You can use the EQUALS and IN selector Condition operators with Get Creative Set-Level Reports and Find Ad Group Creative Sets.

items.name: campaignId
items.desc: The unique identifier for the campaign.

items.name: creationTime
items.desc: The creation date and time of the Creative Set.

items.name: creativeSetId
items.desc: The unique identifier for the Creative Set that belongs to an ad group.You can use the EQUALS, IN, and STARTSWITH selector Condition operators with Get Creative Set-Level Reports.

items.name: creativeSetLanguage
items.desc: The language of the Creative Set.

items.name: creativeSetLanguageDisplayName
items.desc: The language that displays for the Creative Set.

items.name: creativeSetName
items.desc: The name of the Creative Set.You can use the EQUALS, IN, STARTSWITH, CONTAINS, and ENDSWITH selector Condition operators with Get Creative Set-Level Reports.

items.name: deleted
items.desc: An indicator of whether the Creative Set is soft-deleted.You can use the EQUALS and IN selector Condition operators with Get Creative Set-Level Reports.

items.name: displayStatus
items.desc: An indicator of the status of the campaign. The status resolves according to servingStatus and additional criteria.You can use the EQUALS and IN selector Condition operators with Get Creative Set-Level Reports.

items.name: modificationTime
items.desc: The date and time of the most recent modification of the object.

items.name: orgId
items.desc: The id of your account in the Apple Search Ads UI.
